nd Wilbur S  Hinman  Jr  Research Awards  and the Faculty Scholarships for Merit and many others  Numerous awards recognizing the accomplishments of cadets are presented  Awards are presented by civic groups and the Institute  as well as the ROTC components  All persons attending should be seated no later than 15 minutes before start  This event is open to all whom wish to attend  For handicap seating and more information contact the Dean s Office at  540  464 7212  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 